  <description type="morphology">Plants clustered in loose to compact tufts, black or brown with age. Stems ca. 4–10
        cm, central strand absent; rhizoids forming a “hold-fast,” occasionally extending from stem
        and abaxial surface of leaves. Leaves erect to patent when dry, when present pseudocosta
        marginal [submarginal]; apex often cucullate. Outer perichaetial leaves one-third shorter
        than inner leaves. Vaginula forming a sheath around proximal third or fourth of seta. Seta
        1/3–1/2 capsule length. Capsule glossy black with age, columella when dry appearing
        longitudinally ribbed, when wet expanding, becoming stoutly cylindrical or ovoid. Spores
        30–55 µm.</description>
